SECRET_KEY=
DEBUG=
DATABASE_URL=
ALLOWED_HOSTS=

# Railway deployment checklist:
# 1. Push this project to GitHub.
# 2. Create a new Railway project from the GitHub repository.
# 3. Add a PostgreSQL database service in Railway.
# 4. Copy the Railway PostgreSQL DATABASE_URL into the web service variables if Railway does not inject it automatically.
# 5. Set SECRET_KEY to a strong random value.
# 6. Set DEBUG=False.
# 7. Set ALLOWED_HOSTS=.railway.app,.up.railway.app,your-custom-domain.com
# 8. Deploy the service and confirm the build runs collectstatic and migrate.
# 9. Open the Railway domain and test /, /register/, /login/, /dashboard/, /leaderboard/, /invite/, and /donate/.
# 10. Create a Django superuser with Railway shell: python manage.py createsuperuser
